Kirthika ‚Äì Student Counsellor, Periyapalaiyam & Thalambur Campus Contact: +919962506264 Email: in The prominent cultural festivals and events at Vels Institute of Science, Technology & Advanced Studies (VISTAS), Pallavaram include: ‚óè VELS NAKSHATRA: The grand cultural festival featuring a wide array of events such as short films, choreography nights, IPL auctions, and various competitions spread over multiple days with significant prize money. ‚óè VELS STARS: Ahighly anticipated cultural fest dedicated to showcasing student talents in various performing arts and cultural activities. ‚óè CHRYSALIS: Atechnical symposium with workshops and symposium sessions.

‚óè PRAVESHA: Atechnical workshop and symposium event. ‚óè Other events include celebrations like Freshers Day, Onam celebration, White Coat Ceremony, Cadet Ceremony, and Annual Day. Campus Navigation Data The following are static step-by-step directions between key campus locations at VISTAS. ‚óè From Gate 1: ‚óã To Shivalaya Block: Go straight till Ambedkar Block. To your right is Shivalaya Block. ‚óã To Edison Block: Go straight from Gate 1 to Ambedkar Block, then take a right at Jeevan Sandwiches. Turn left and go straight to find Edison Block. ‚óã To Ruby Girls Hostel: Walk past Ambedkar Block and New Library Block. Ruby Girls Hostel is ahead on your left. ‚óè From Shivalaya Block: ‚óã To Jeevan Sandwiches: Turn right from Shivalaya Block and you‚Äôll see Jeevan Sandwiches next door. ‚óã To Edison Block: From Shivalaya Block, head towards Jeevan Sandwiches, take a right, then a left to reach Edison Block. ‚óè From Edison Block: ‚óã To Guest House: Exit Edison Block and walk straight past Fleming Block. The Guest House is right ahead.

‚óè From Ambedkar Block: ‚óã To Vinayagar Temple: Facing Ambedkar Block, walk left. The Vinayagar Temple is close to the junction near Bank/ATM. ‚óè From Pearl Girls Hostel: ‚óã To Ruby Girls Hostel: Walk south along the inner road. Ruby Girls Hostel is next to Steve Jobs Block. ‚óè From VOC Block: ‚óã To Einstein Block: Exit VOC Block and head right. Einstein Block is next door. ‚óè From New Library Block: ‚óã To Central Library Block: Walk straight and you will reach Central Library Block just behind the New Library Block. ‚óè From Steve Jobs Block: ‚óã To Restaurant: The restaurant is located right behind Steve Jobs Block. ‚óè From Dr. MGR Block: ‚óã To Bank/ATM: Walk straight past Ratan Tata Block. Bank/ATM is at the intersection.

üè† Hostel & Accommodation VISTAS provides clean and well-maintained hostels for both boys and girls. ‚óè Girls: Pearl & Ruby Hostels ‚óè Boys: Sapphire & Diamond Hostels Facilities include laundry, hygienic mess food, common areas, and 24/7 security. üìå Visiting Hours: 7:00 AM ‚Äì 9:00 PM (daily). üìö Library The campus library is located between Flemingo Block and Sir V. Raman Block. Students can use the library during breaks; entry is not allowed during class hours. Library Rules: ‚óè Sign the register with your name and entry time upon arrival. ‚óè To borrow a book, provide your email ID to the librarian, who will record the due date. ‚óè Upon leaving, sign the register again with your exit time. üìå Bonafide Certificate Request Students who require a Bonafide Certificate are requested to write a letter addressed to the Registrar, get it duly signed by their Class Incharge and then by the HOD, and submit it at the office in the MGR Block. If the Bonafide Certificate is required with the fee structure, the signed letter should be submitted at the MGR Block office located on the left side of the entrance. If the Bonafide Certificate is required without the fee structure, the signed letter should be submitted at the Registrar‚Äôs office, which is located on the right side of the entrance of the MGR Block.

üìå Incubation Centre ‚Äì Business Ideas Have a business idea or startup idea? üöÄ Visit the Incubation Centre on the 2nd floor of the Edison Block and share your proposal with the team for guidance and support. üöå Transport Facility Transport is available for day scholars who have paid for the service, covering routes within Chennai. ü•§ Vending Machines Vending machines are available at MGR Block, Flemingo Block, and Steve Jobs Block for snacks and beverages. Canteens There are 3 canteens on campus: SSS Canteen, Jeevan canteen, and Food Court, offering a variety of food and beverages for students and staff. üõï Temple & School ‚óè Temple: Asmall temple dedicated to Lord Ganesh is located inside the VISTAS campus for students and staff to offer prayers. ‚óè School: VELS VIDHYASHRAM is situated within the campus, providing education for school-level students.
